{"author":{"id":"30a9cdd9e5369167dc36be4d3e5f98e516aa30b7571a17013bc815eef45f09c3"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1452356826,"nonce":"LP5oZtJ3N2UimdImD9WPbvQjopA=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDE3MDI1NzY5Mg==","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/522#issuecomment-170257692"},"message":"\u003e We can do this. But we need to get all on board I guess and integrate it deeply with bioaRchigve and cargo-port.\n\nI think everyone is on board, judging by comments I've read. I don't know about the \"deep integrations\", we can figure out some of that later. cargo-port is feature complete, it is just a dumb tarball store, that's it. bioaRchive has room for features, so maybe there's work to be done there.\n\n\u003e Hehe, see here: \"If conda can handle such cases I guess it would be easier for us to integrate this directly into bioaRchive instead of doing this on demand on pushing regularly to bioconda.\" from bioconda/bioconda-recipes#574 (comment) :)\n\nI'm not understanding why you're pushing bioaRchive integration so much -- we do so much more than just R packages. If you want packages in a conda repo, we should set up hooks in bioaRchive to automatically push packages to the conda repo, but maybe this is what you meant.\n\nwe should be doing on-demand pushing to our own channel, which changes the problem quite a lot\n\n\u003e They are not really aware of the problem I guess. Or we are just to radical.\n\nhah, ok.\n\n\u003e We have a lot of binaries, e.g starforge can be more or less replaced by conda if we do it right and at least this can/should be shared with bioconda. In the end it does not matter if we activate 3 or 4 channels by default. What I really like to avoid is to just recreate recipes because we have a more strict police.\n\nsure, understood, agreed.\n\n\u003e I'm volunteering to write such things and include it into the best practice IUC repository as soon as it is more clear how do we want to proceed here. A dedicated hackathon would be also nice. Most of my porting time is spend in compiling and writing tests, so I could need help here :)\n\nhappy to help @bgruening, just assign me issues :)","files":null}]}